<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1775" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1775">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 033.1100 K77/71.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Secretary of State and his party will arrive March 10 at Acajutla,
                            will remain at San Salvador the 11th and 12th, and will leave on the
                            13th for San José, Guatemala.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>